<p>With this command I can terminate all connections running in a specific database.</p>  <pre><code>SELECT pg_terminate_backend(pg_stat_activity.pid)  FROM pg_stat_activity  WHERE pg_stat_activity.datname = 'DATABASE_NAME'  AND pid &lt;&gt; pg_backend_pid(); </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to terminate connections in a certain schema only?</p>